<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: NES 2.0 inadequate to represent game region and peripher]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7071&amp;p=68895#p68895"><![CDATA[
<div class="quotetitle">Dwedit wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />Obviously, this is an issue with Nestopia being too reliant on the ROM database, but wasn't NES 2.0 designed to answer the ambiguous questions that a ROM database would otherwise solve?<br /></div><br /><br />Yes, I did plan on having a controller designation field on 2.0.  <br /><br />Since I have been going over my FPGA NES again lately (converting it from schematic entry to verilog)  I have been tinkering with the inner guts some more, and I was going to write up my NES 2.0 submappers and things.<br /><br /><br />As a heads-up on what I have done with 2.0, I converted all of the GoodNES stuff that needed a special database into 2.0 ROMs so my loader didn't need said database.   I just sorta failed to document it.  whoops.  <br /><br />So now I have been going back over it and documenting the stuff that I figured out.  <br /><br />If there's still enough interest I will polish up the spec with a complete list of games that benefit from 2.0 along with headers (or ips or whatever) for them.<br /><br />note that this includes a good 50% or more of the Vs games-  I actually bought 20 or so Vs games off of ebay to acquire this information, along with RGB PPU palettes and custom lockout chips present on the Namco Vs. games.<br /><br />If there's anything else that should be added to the 2.0 header, let me know.  I hear a call for controller type (which is a good idea).  Would a system type flag(Fami, NES) be beneficial if it had a controller field?<br /><br />The Vs. fields include PPU type, namco "custom" (their designation) chip type, and I believe controller mapping.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=230">kevtris</a> — Tue Oct 19, 2010 8:20 am</p><hr />
